g.text: This example shows an actuator that consists of a proportional
4-way directional valve driving a double-acting hydraulic cylinder.
The cylinder drives a load consisting of a mass, viscous and
Coulomb friction, constant force, and a spring. The actuator is
powered by a variable-displacement, pressure-compensated pump,
driven by a constant velocity motor. Pipelines between the valve,
